luding the activation, recirculation and homing of T-lymphocytes, hematopoiesis, inflammation and response to bacterial infection (PubMed:7528188). Engages, through its ectodomain, extracellular matrix components such as hyaluronan/HA, collagen, growth factors, cytokines or proteases and serves as a platform for signal transduction by assembling, via its cytoplasmic domain, protein complexes containing receptor kinases and membrane proteases (PubMed:18757307, PubMed:23589287). Such effectors include PKN2, the RhoGTPases RAC1 and RHOA, Rho-kinases and phospholipase C that coordinate signaling pathways promoting calcium mobilization and actin-mediated cytoskeleton reorganization essential for cell migration and adhesion (PubMed:15123640). {ECO:0000269|PubMed:15123640, ECO:0000269|PubMed:16541107, ECO:0000269|PubMed:18757307, ECO:0000269|PubMed:19703720, ECO:0000269|PubMed:22726066, ECO:0000269|PubMed:23589287, ECO:0000269|PubMed:7528188}."], "subcellular_locations": [{"location": "Cell membrane", "source": "uniprot", "termSL": "SL-0039", "labelSL": "Cellular component"}, {"location": "Cell projection", "source": "uniprot", "termSL": "SL-0280", "labelSL": "Cellular component"}, {"location": "Secreted", "source": "uniprot", "termSL": "SL-0243", "labelSL": "Cellular component"}, {"location": "Plasma membrane", "source": "HPA_main", "termSL": "SL-0039", "labelSL": "Cell membrane"}, {"location": "Golgi apparatus", "source": "HPA_additional", "termSL": "SL-0132", "labelSL": "Golgi apparatus"}, {"location": "Predicted to be secreted", "source": "HPA_extracellular_location", "termSL": null, "labelSL": null}], "obsolete_symbols": [{"label": "MIC4", "source": "HGNC"}, {"label": "MDU2", "source": "HGNC"}, {"label": "MDU3", "source": "HGNC"}], "obsolete_names": [{"label": "CD44 antigen (homing function and Indian blood group system)", "source": "HGNC"}], "protein_ids": [{"id": "P16070", "source": "uniprot_swissprot"}, {"id": "E9PKC6", "source": "uniprot_trembl"}, {"id": "H0Y2P0",